node.text:
We’re launching a Tuesday TIP OF THE WEEK series to help answer some commonly asked questions from our community! Today we’re kicking off with our friend @takebetterphotosofyourdog 📸 

Every dog deserves a great portrait. But it’s not always possible to hire a professional photographer, and most people don’t own a DSLR or mirrorless camera. Luckily, cell phones come with pretty good built-in cameras these days!

Watch this video for a list of tips that'll help you be a better photographer - with your cell phone! Be sure to ready our blog (LINK IN BIO) or download the guide on www.dogphototips.com 

We’ll focus one week a month on how to take better photos of your dog, so leave your questions in the comments and tune back in next month for the answers! 

Check out more tips from Take Better Photos of Your Dog: @takebetterphotosofyourdog
Cover photo: @marshygsp 

#dogphotography #takebetterphotosofyourdog #photographytips #tuesdaytip #dogsofinstagram #tipoftheweek #phototips #dogphotos #dogphotoshoot

node.title: How To Take Better Photos of Your Dog With Your Phone

By now, you've probably heard how CBD can be beneficial for both humans and pets alike. For those new to the conversation, CBD is a derived from hemp or cannabis and does not contain THC, which is the substance that produces a high for its users. 

In 2018, a Cornell study reported 80% of osteoarthritis dogs who used CBD showed “significant improvement in pain levels and quality of life”. 

In a world where too many pets are homeless, abandoned, or returned, CBD seems to offer a ray of hope. The potential to steady a dog’s nerves long enough to charm a family, relieve a joint pain, aid in separation anxiety, or help behave when meeting new people could make all the difference in a pet’s life. Incorporating CBD into a consistent routine is one practice that can support this transition and pave the way for calm, happy families. 

Link in bio to read more about how CBD can help animals or donate a CBD product to a shelter pet through @welovecuddly!

We’re celebrating our TEN YEAR ANNIVERSARY by featuring some of our tops posts over the past ten years in a Greatest Photo of All Time Contest! Head to the link in our bio to vote on your favorite photo over the last decade of @dogsofinstagram! 

The photo with the most votes will be turned into our next NFT (non-fungible token) to be auctioned off to raise money for pet welfare organizations.

Ready, set…vote for the greatest photo of all time!

When you’ve got good good news to share and can hardly contain your excitement…FURRIENDS! We can finally announce, we’ve just released our very first NFT (non-fungible token) of our very first post ten years ago! Swipe ➡️ to see what it is! (Anyone remember those OG Instagram filters? 🙈)

Own a piece of history by purchasing the first ever post made on our world-famous @dogsofinstagram account. This is a one of a kind commemorative version of the post, created as part of our 10 year anniversary. 50% of the proceeds from this sale will be donated to animal welfare organizations.

This one-of-a-kind NFT auction ends Sunday, so place your bids while you can! LINK IN BIO TO PLACE YOUR BID TODAY 💸 

What’s an NFT? A non-fungible token (NFT) is a unit of data stored on a digital ledger, called a blockchain, that certifies a digital asset to be unique and therefore not interchangeable. NFTs can be used to represent items such as photos, videos, audio, and other types of digital files. NFTs are designed to give you something that can't be copied: ownership of the work. To put it in terms of physical art collecting: anyone can buy a Monet print. But only one person can own the original.
